
* ban *

Usage: ban site/user/new <partial site/user name>


Site = Ban Entire Site fron logging in
New  = Ban only new users from a site from loggin in
user = Ban just a specific user name


This command will ban either a site or a user, the names of which are written
to the files in the SITEBAN and USERBAN macros.

** Note:  When banning sites, you're best to use a partial site, i.e.
          to ban dialin23.ppp.myisp.com  you should use:
	  .ban site myisp.com  or for ips use:  .ban new xxx.xxx.xxx.
	  Omit the last number of the number address.

See: unban, listbans
